=RBSIA=
//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_image_audit}

NOTE: This operation produces a flat catalog of hallmark identifiers in
{rbtgi_repository}
via the GAR REST API implemented by
{gar_service}.
Identifiers only — no per-member presence detail (use {rbtgo_image_rekon} for that), and no health classification (use {rbtgo_hallmark_tally} for that).
Captured upstream artifacts are not audited here — base images and reliquary cohorts are now {rbtga_lode}s (bole and conclave kinds), enumerated by {rbtgo_lode_divine}.

The
{rbtr_director}
audits one domain:

* `rbfl_audit_hallmarks` — every hallmark identifier under the `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/` root

Audit vs. {rbtgo_hallmark_tally}: audit is a {rbtr_director}-tier flat-list operation; tally is a {rbtr_retriever}-tier operation that classifies each entry by basename completeness and vouch status.
The two roles compose without overlap.

== Hallmarks Audit

The
{rbtr_director}
audits hallmark identifiers:

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Packages Under Hallmarks Root*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«HALLMARKS_ROOT»` from `RBGL_HALLMARKS_ROOT` (kindled from `RBGC_GAR_CATEGORY_HALLMARKS`, the token `rbi_hm`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REPO_BASE»` as the GAR REST API repository base (`projects/«PROJECT»/locations/«REGION»/repositories/«REPOSITORY»`)
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[GAR REST API: packages.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages?pageSize=1000`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. Extract `.packages[].name`, strip the resource prefix, URL-decode `%2F` back to `/`, and retain only entries beginning with `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»/`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«HALLMARK_ROWS»` as `«HALLMARK» «BASENAME»` pairs derived from those entries (a 2-deep enumeration shared with {rbtgo_image_rekon})

//axhos_step
. *Project to Unique Identifiers*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«HALLMARKS»` as the ordered set of distinct hallmark identifiers from the first column of `«HALLMARK_ROWS»`

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_ark}
. *Display Results*:
.. If `«HALLMARKS»` is empty:
... {rbbc_show}
"No hallmarks found under «HALLMARKS_ROOT»/"
... return success with count `0`
.. Otherwise:
... {rbbc_show}
table header `HALLMARK`
... For each `«HALLMARK»` in `«HALLMARKS»`:
.... {rbbc_show}
`«HALLMARK»`
... {rbbc_show}
"Total hallmarks: «COUNT»"

//axhoc_completion
The procedure completes successfully when the ordered list of identifiers — possibly empty — has been displayed and the count line emitted.
The empty case is non-fatal: an empty domain reports zero rather than failing, since "registry holds no entries in this domain" is a valid director observation, not an error.
=RBTDRO29=
// Disposition: StateProgressing. Build-only — no charge, no test. Cases stop
// when each handbook-prescribed hallmark lands in GAR. Per-case precondition
// probes enable a-la-carte single-case rerun.
//
// conclave_reliquary yokes the reliquary stamp into vessel rbrv.env files
// and commits. Downstream cases verify it ran by reading RBRV_RELIQUARY from
// a stable yoked vessel's rbrv.env — no out-of-source-tree scratch state.

use std::io::{BufRead, BufReader, Write};
=RBTDRO140=

/// Forge-vessel slot the bole election rewrites (its single ORIGIN slot).
const RBTDRO_FORGE_BASE_ANCHOR_VAR: &str = "RBRV_IMAGE_1_ANCHOR";

/// Bole touchmark chaining fact ensconce writes to current/. Mirrors
/// rbgc_constants.sh RBF_FACT_LODE_TOUCHMARK.
const RBTDRO_FACT_LODE_TOUCHMARK: &str = "rbf_fact_lode_touchmark";

/// GAR Lode namespace root in an elected anchor locator. Mirrors
/// rbgc_constants.sh RBGC_GAR_CATEGORY_LODES.
const RBTDRO_LODE_ROOT: &str = "rbi_ld";

/// Bole member tag in an elected anchor locator. Mirrors rbgc_constants.sh
/// RBGC_LODE_TAG_BOLE.
const RBTDRO_LODE_TAG_BOLE: &str = "rbi_bole";

// ── Reliquary stamp witness ──────────────────────────────────

/// Filename of a vessel's rbrv.env (relative to the vessel directory).
const RBTDRO_VESSEL_RBRV_FILE: &str = "rbrv.env";

=RBTDRO218=
    Ok(())
}

/// Cases 3-7 probe: reliquary stamp yoked into the witness vessel's rbrv.env.
/// Case 1's yoke fan-out writes RBRV_RELIQUARY into every ordain-path vessel
/// and commits; reading the witness vessel's committed value is the cross-case
/// evidence that case 1 ran. No out-of-source-tree scratch state.
=RBTDRO363=
    Ok((hallmark, gar_root, ark_stem))
}

/// Yoke the reliquary stamp into every vessel's rbrv.env. The yoke tabtarget
/// validates the stamp once against GAR, then wildcard-iterates every vessel
/// under ${RBRR_VESSEL_DIR}. The orchestrator commits the resulting rbrv.env
/// changes after this primitive returns.
=RBTDRO778=
/// Probe: reliquary scratch present (confirms case 1 completed).
fn rbtdro_onboarding_kludge_tadmor(dir: &Path) -> rbtdre_Verdict {
    let probe = rbtdrb_Probe {
        name: "reliquary stamp captured",
        check: rbtdro_probe_reliquary_stamp,
        remediation: "rerun rbtdro_onboarding_conclave_reliquary before this case",
    };
=RBTDRO1041=
/// airgap vessel's base anchor (no copy — orchestration writes the locator
/// directly), conjure the airgap bottle.
/// Case 1 yoked the reliquary stamp into both forge and airgap vessels.
/// Propagates airgap-bottle hallmark to moriah via RBRN_BOTTLE_HALLMARK.
fn rbtdro_onboarding_ordain_airgap_chain(dir: &Path) -> rbtdre_Verdict {
    let probe = rbtdrb_Probe {
        name: "reliquary stamp captured",
        check: rbtdro_probe_reliquary_stamp,
        remediation: "rerun rbtdro_onboarding_conclave_reliquary before this case",
=RBTDRU165=
/// merely a portability one.
///
/// This list is the single tool floor for BOTH step languages: bash
/// command-position tokens and python `subprocess` argv[0] literals are
/// classified against the same membership (one floor, two languages).
pub(crate) const ZRBTDRU_GCB_ALLOWED: &[&str] = &[
    "apt-get", "awk", "cat", "curl", "cut", "docker",
    // gcloud adjudicated 2026-06-10: rbgjv02's SLSA provenance describe
    // subprocess-runs it in the cloud-sdk builder where it is native;
    // REST conversion deferred.
    "gcloud",
    "gcrane", "gpg",
    "grep", "head", "ls", "openssl", "sha256sum", "shasum",
    "tar", "tr", "wget",
];

=RBFDCHECK=
70:  readonly ZRBFD_MIRROR_PREFIX="${BURD_TEMP_DIR}/rbfd_mirror_"
73:  readonly ZRBFD_GRAFT_PREFIX="${BURD_TEMP_DIR}/rbfd_graft_"
990:rbfd_ordain() {
1015:  # then elects inside rbfd_build, bind gates inside rbfd_mirror, graft is
1016:  # deliberately ungated (see the comment in rbfd_graft).
1018:    rbnve_conjure) rbfd_build "${z_vessel_dir}" ;;
1019:    rbnve_bind)    rbfd_mirror "${z_vessel_dir}" ;;
1020:    rbnve_graft)   rbfd_graft "${z_vessel_dir}" ;;

