//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_director_yoke}

NOTE: This operation writes `RBRV_RELIQUARY=«TOUCHMARK»` into every vessel's {rbrv_regime} file under `${RBRR_VESSEL_DIR}` so that subsequent Cloud Build operations (conjure, bind, graft, enshrine) consume the named tool image set as GCB step images.
The about/vouch pipeline (gcloud, docker, alpine, syft) consumes reliquary tool images uniformly across all ordain modes; bind additionally uses gcrane for image-copy.
The touchmark is validated once against GAR before any vessel file is touched: the conclave Lode package `{gar_lodes_namespace}/«TOUCHMARK»` must exist and carry all six expected tool cohort member tags as `:rbi_<tool>` sprued tags — one per tool — on that single package.
On touchmark validation failure the operation errors diagnostically without writing any vessel.
On per-vessel write failure the diagnostic identifies the failing vessel and the set of vessels already written, so the operator can resume from a known point.
This primitive does not commit; the caller (orchestrator or operator) commits the {rbrv_regime} changes.

The
{rbtr_director}
yokes a reliquary touchmark across every vessel:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtr_director}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«TOUCHMARK»` provided as first positional argument (e.g., `r260327172456`)

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *List Conclave Lode Tags in GAR*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` as `${RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX}d-${RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (resolved by `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GAR_REPOSITORY»` as `${RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX}${RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER}-gar` (resolved by `RBDC_GAR_REPOSITORY`)
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages.tags/list[tags.list] for the package
`{gar_lodes_namespace}/«TOUCHMARK»`
under
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
/
{rbrd_gcp_region}
/
`«GAR_REPOSITORY»`
with `pageSize=1000`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response — a 404 here means the conclave Lode package does not exist
.. Filter response tag names to those matching the sprue prefix `rbi_` (constant `RBGC_LODE_TAG_SPRUE`), excluding `:rbi_vouch`
.. Strip the sprue prefix to yield the bare tool-name set present in GAR

//axhos_step
. *Verify Tool Cohort Completeness*:
.. Expected tool name set: `gcloud`, `docker`, `alpine`, `syft`, `binfmt`, `gcrane` (per
{rbtgo_lode_conclave})
.. {rbbc_require}
all six names present in the filtered list — verified as `:rbi_<tool>` member tags on the single `{gar_lodes_namespace}/«TOUCHMARK»` package
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if any expected tool is missing — the error message names `«TOUCHMARK»`, the Lode package path, and the specific missing tool(s); remediation points at
{rbtgo_lode_conclave}

//axhos_step
. *Iterate Vessels under `${RBRR_VESSEL_DIR}`*:
.. Enumerate every immediate subdirectory of `${RBRR_VESSEL_DIR}` containing an {rbrv_regime} file
.. {rbbc_require}
at least one vessel found — empty enumeration is a fatal error (nothing to yoke)
.. For each enumerated vessel, perform *Rewrite the {rbrv_regime}* below in directory order
.. Maintain a running list of vessels successfully written; emit per-vessel progress

//axhos_step
. *Rewrite the {rbrv_regime}* (per vessel):
.. Load the vessel's {rbrv_regime} file into memory, line by line
.. For each line matching `^RBRV_RELIQUARY=` — substitute with `RBRV_RELIQUARY=«TOUCHMARK»`, preserving position
.. All other lines pass through unchanged
.. If no `RBRV_RELIQUARY=` line was found — append one under a `# Tool Image Reliquary` comment header
.. Write the composed content to a per-vessel temp file, then atomically replace the {rbrv_regime} file via rename
.. {rbbc_fatal}
on any per-vessel I/O failure — the error message names the failing vessel and the list of vessels already written, so the operator can resume from a known point

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution writes `RBRV_RELIQUARY=«TOUCHMARK»` into the {rbrv_regime} file of every vessel discovered under `${RBRR_VESSEL_DIR}`; no GAR state is modified.
The primitive does not commit — the caller (orchestrator or operator) commits the modified {rbrv_regime} files with their usual git workflow.
The reliquary tool images are now linked, but vessel images must be rebuilt
({rbtgo_ark_ordain})
to pick up the new tool versions.

//axhrb_regime
{rbrd_regime}

This regime specifies depot-time-immutable identity and infrastructure settings.
Each
{rbrd_regime}
instance pins the values that
{rbtgo_depot_levy}
consumes at depot creation — the identity tuple `(RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX, RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER)` (from which depot project ID, GAR repository, pool stem, and bucket fall out as RBDC constants), the GCP region, and the Cloud Build private worker pool machine type.
RBRD assignment files are found in the operator's local filesystem and are frozen for the productive lifetime of the depot.
Changing any field after levy requires a fresh depot.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrd_group_depot_identity}

The cloud-namespace identity tuple consumed by
{rbtgo_depot_levy}
to derive every depot-scoped GCP resource name.
Both fields must be populated — the marshal-zero path blanks them so a fresh regime requires an explicit operator decision before `rbrd_validate` passes.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrd_cloud_prefix}

Prefix prepended to all cloud-visible resource names under the depot: GAR image paths, vessel package names,
{gcb_service}
substitutions, and other GCP-scoped identifiers.
Must be 2–11 characters, start with a lowercase letter, and end with a hyphen (regex `^[a-z][a-z0-9-]*-$`).

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrd_depot_moniker}

Stem identifier that combines with
{rbrd_cloud_prefix}
to form the depot identity tuple.
Must be 1–26 characters, start with a lowercase letter, and contain only lowercase alphanumerics (regex `^[a-z][a-z0-9]*$`).
The tuple derives `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID`, `RBDC_GAR_REPOSITORY`, `RBDC_GCB_POOL_STEM`, and `RBDC_GCS_BUCKET` at kindle time.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrd_group_region}

The default
{gcp_service}
region for regional services like
{gar_service}
and
{gcb_service}.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrd_gcp_region}

Applied when creating repositories and submitting builds unless overridden by operation-specific configuration.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrd_group_pool}

{gcb_service}
private worker pool configuration consumed at pool creation time by
{rbtgo_depot_levy}.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrd_gcb_machine_type}

Compute Engine machine type for the private worker pool.
Valid families: `e2`, `n2d`, `c3`.
Examples: `e2-standard-2`, `e2-highcpu-8`, `n2d-standard-4`.
Pool scales to zero workers when idle — no idle cost accrues.

//axhro_kindle
{rbkro_kindle}

Kindles the {rbrd_regime} fields by enrolling each field with its type-specific constraints under named groups.
Detects unexpected RBRD_ variables.
Locks the regime against further modification.

//axhro_validate
{rbkro_validate}

Validates enrolled fields against type-specific constraints from enrollment.
Enforces format constraints on {rbrd_cloud_prefix} and {rbrd_depot_moniker}, and the joint-length cap on `${RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX}d-${RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (≤30 chars per the GCP project ID limit).

//axhro_render
{rbkro_render}

Renders the {rbrd_regime} grouped by section with presentation gates per group.
Sections: Depot Identity, GCP Region, Google Cloud Build Pool.

[[rbrd_tripwire]]
{rbrd_tripwire}::
A `FROM scratch` GAR image carrying the verbatim {rbrd_regime} assignment file, inscribed at `«REGION»-docker.pkg.dev/«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»/«GAR_REPOSITORY»/rbi_df/rbrd:tripwire`.
The tripwire makes the depot-time-immutable contract enforceable: because every RBDC-derived resource name (project ID, GAR repository, pool stem, bucket) is computed from the {rbrd_regime} at kindle time, a silent post-levy edit of the {rbrd_regime} assignment file would point subsequent operations at a different depot identity or worker-pool configuration than the one actually provisioned.
+
The tripwire is _produced_ exactly once, host-side, at the tail of
{rbtgo_depot_levy}
— after the depot-tracking refresh, using the Payor OAuth access token already in scope.
A pre-push existence guard (`docker manifest inspect`) makes inscription idempotent-by-refusal: an already-present tripwire is fatal, since RBRD is frozen for the depot's productive lifetime and refreshing it requires a fresh depot (unmake + relevy).
Inscription also refuses on a working tree with unstaged or staged changes (`bug_require_clean_tree`): the tripwire ships the tracked {rbrd_regime} assignment file's bytes as the depot's permanent drift reference, so the inscribed state must be a committed one.
+
The tripwire is _consumed_ inline by every cloud-submitting command before it dispatches a build: the command pulls the image, extracts the embedded {rbrd_regime} assignment file, and exact-byte-compares it (comments, whitespace, and line ordering all participate) against the local copy.
A mismatch, a missing image, or a registry/auth failure is fatal with recovery guidance — the command refuses to submit cloud work against a drifted or unverifiable depot regime.
The check takes a bearer token parameter and is role-agnostic; each consuming command passes its own role's token (no new IAM grants).
+
The tripwire is depot-scoped operational state, not part of the hallmark / reliquary / enshrine image catalogue; the image enumerators ignore the `rbi_df` namespace by design.
Both operations are implemented host-side (Cloud Build is not involved) by `rbrd_inscribe` and `rbrd_check` in `Tools/rbk/rbndb_base.sh`, exposed for manual use via the `rbw-rdi` (inscribe) and `rbw-rdc` (check) tabtargets.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_hallmark_tally}

NOTE: This operation enumerates every
{rbtga_ark}
in
{rbtgi_repository}
by listing packages under `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/` via the GAR REST API implemented by
{gar_service},
classifying each
{rbtga_hallmark}
by basename presence under its subtree.
A single `packages.list` call returns the full corpus; no per-vessel iteration is required because vessel identity is no longer encoded in the GAR path.

The
{rbtr_retriever}
tallies hallmarks:

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_retriever}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_retriever_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RETRIEVER_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Hallmark Packages*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«HALLMARKS_ROOT»` from `RBGL_HALLMARKS_ROOT` (kindled to `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REPO_BASE»` as the GAR REST API repository base (`projects/«PROJECT»/locations/«REGION»/repositories/«REPOSITORY»`)
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[GAR REST API: packages.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages?pageSize=1000`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «RETRIEVER_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. Extract `.packages[].name` from the response, strip the resource prefix, and URL-decode `%2F` back to `/`
.. Filter to names whose path under `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»/` is exactly two segments (`<hallmark>/<basename>`); excludes both shallower and deeper entries, and excludes anything outside `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/` (reliquaries, enshrines)
.. For each retained `<hallmark>/<basename>` package, {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages.tags/list[GAR REST API: tags.list] for the package and {rbbc_require} at least one tag returned (HTTP 200 with non-empty `.tags[]`). Skip packages with zero tags — these are post-jettison walking-dead: their parent manifest has been deleted by {rbtgo_image_delete} but their orphan children persist until the depot's cleanup policy (see {rbtgo_depot_levy} step *Create Container Repository*) reaps them on its next daily run. Filtering at this read site makes the display reflect the post-jettison user-facing state immediately, decoupling it from GAR's lazy reclamation cadence.
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PAIRS»` as sorted `<hallmark> <basename>` pairs (one per line) for packages with at least one live tag. An empty result is a valid outcome — no hallmarks in the repository.

//axhos_step
. *Classify Health Per Hallmark*:
.. Iterate `«PAIRS»` in sort order; each contiguous run of the same hallmark value constitutes one
{rbtga_hallmark}'s
ark inventory.
.. For each hallmark, record whether the basenames
{rbtga_ark_image},
{rbtga_ark_about},
and
{rbtga_ark_vouch}
each appear in its run. Other basenames (`pouch`, `diags`, `attest`) are retained for display but do not affect health classification.
.. Classify:
... `vouched`: `image` + `about` + `vouch` all present
... `pending`: `image` + `about` present, `vouch` absent
... `incomplete`: any other combination (including `image` without `about`, `about` without `image`, or only auxiliary basenames)

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_hallmark}
. *Display Table*:
.. {rbbc_show}
three-column header: `HALLMARK`, `HEALTH`, `BASENAMES`
.. For each hallmark (in sort order):
... {rbbc_show}
hallmark, health state, space-separated list of basenames present under its subtree
.. {rbbc_show}
summary line: `Total hallmarks: N (vouched: V, pending: P, incomplete: I)`

//axhos_step
. *Recommend Next Actions*:
.. If any `pending` hallmarks:
... {rbbc_show}
tabtarget recommendation: {rbtgo_director_vouch} (`rbw-fV`)
.. If any `incomplete` hallmarks:
... {rbbc_show}
tabtarget recommendation: {rbtgo_ark_abjure} (`rbw-fA`) — incomplete typically means the build was interrupted or the about stitch failed

//axhoc_completion
Procedure completes successfully when the packages listing returns and the classified table displays.
No resources are modified.
Vessel identity is not encoded in the GAR path; restoration of a vessel column, if needed, reads `vessel_name` from `about` or `vouch` metadata and is AAL scope — not performed by tally.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_image_rekon}

NOTE: This operation reports which canonical members are present under a
hallmark subtree in
{rbtgi_repository}
via the GAR REST API implemented by
{gar_service}.
Raw presence enumeration — no health classification (use {rbtgo_hallmark_tally} for that).

The
{rbtr_director}
rekons one domain:

* `rbfl_rekon_hallmark` — basenames present under a hallmark subtree

Rekon over reliquary cohorts and the legacy enshrinement domain is intentionally omitted: a reliquary is now a conclave {rbtga_lode} whose member tags are inspected via its Lode augur operation, and an enshrinement is a single image per anchor (1-deep), so neither warrants a presence table here — {rbtgo_image_audit} covers the catalog and {rbtgo_image_retrieve} covers retrieval.

== Hallmark Rekon

The
{rbtr_director}
