Tools/rbk/vov_veiled/RBS0-SpecTop.adoc:1436:The {rbtr_director} submits a two-step Cloud Build job — gcrane capture of the upstream manifest, then a vouch push — writing the {rbtga_lode_vouch} provenance envelope to its one canonical home, the `:rbi_vouch` tag in GAR, and handing the touchmark forward host-side as the {rbf_fact_lode}.
Tools/rbk/vov_veiled/RBS0-SpecTop.adoc:1448:The {rbtr_director} submits a two-step Cloud Build job — gcrane capture of the tool cohort, then a vouch push — writing the {rbtga_lode_vouch} provenance envelope to its one canonical home, the `:rbi_vouch` tag in GAR, and handing the touchmark forward host-side as the {rbf_fact_lode}.
Tools/rbk/vov_veiled/RBS0-SpecTop.adoc:1460:The {rbtr_director} submits a two-step Cloud Build job — curl fetch with GPG-verified published-checksum verification and opaque-blob wrap, then a vouch push — writing the {rbtga_lode_vouch} provenance envelope to its one canonical home, the `:rbi_vouch` tag in GAR, and handing the touchmark forward host-side as the {rbf_fact_lode}.
Tools/rbk/vov_veiled/RBS0-SpecTop.adoc:1473:The {rbtr_director} submits a four-step Cloud Build job — a python select step that reads the upstream OCI index and picks the curated `{disktype × arch}` leaves by descriptor, a gcrane copy-by-digest, a blob-residency guard, then a vouch push — writing the {rbtga_lode_vouch} provenance envelope to its one canonical home, the `:rbi_vouch` tag in GAR, and handing the touchmark forward host-side as the {rbf_fact_lode}.
Tools/rbk/vov_veiled/RBS0-SpecTop.adoc:2171:Minted host-side before submission, so the touchmark is known before the build (the host owns the stamp in order to write the {rbf_fact_lode}).
Tools/rbk/vov_veiled/RBS0-SpecTop.adoc:2191:It has one canonical home: the in-GAR `:rbi_vouch` tag (the Lode self-describing in the registry, decoded by {rbtgo_lode_augur}). The host-side {rbf_fact_lode} carries only the bare touchmark, not the envelope — so reading host-side provenance costs a GAR call, the accepted price of a single canonical home.
